h1101.definition: a primitive root; (also	denominatively from {{h1098}}) to fodder; to overflow (specifically with oil.); by implication, to mix; to fodder; anoint, confound, × fade, mingle, mix (self), give provender, temper.

h1102.definition: a primitive root; to muzzle; be held in.

h1103.definition: a primitive root; to pinch sycamore figs (a process necessary to ripen them); gatherer.

h1104.definition: a primitive root; to make away with (specifically by swallowing); generally, to destroy; cover, destroy, devour, eat up, be at end, spend up, swallow down (up).

h1105.definition: from {{h1104}}; a gulp; figuratively, destruction; devouring, that which he hath swallowed up.

h1106.definition: the same as {{h1105}}; Bela, the name of a place, also of an Edomite and of two Israelites; Bela.

h1107.definition: or בַּלְעֲדֵי; constructive plural from {{h1077}} and {{h5703}}, not till, i.e. (as preposition or adverb); except, without, besides; beside, not (in), save, without.

h1108.definition: patronymically from {{h1106}}; a Belaite (collectively) or descendants of Bela; Belaites.

h1109.definition: probably from {{h1077}} and {{h5971}}; not (of the) people, i.e. foreigner; Bilam, a Mesopotamian prophet; also a place in Palestine; Balaam, Bileam.

h1110.definition: a primitive root; to annihilate; (make) waste.

h1111.definition: from {{h1110}}; waster; Balak, a Moabitish king; Balak.

h1112.definition: or בֵּלְאשַׁצַּרlemma בֵּלְאשַׁצּר missing vowel, corrected to בֵּלְאשַׁצַּר; of foreign origin (compare {{h1095}}); Belshatstsar, a Babylonian king; Belshazzar.

h1114.definition: of uncertain derivation; Bilshan, an Israelite; Bilshan.

h1115.definition: constructive feminine of {{h1086}} (equivalent to {{h1097}}); properly, a failure of, i.e. (used only as a negative particle, usually with a prepositional prefix) not, except, without, unless, besides, because not, until, etc.; because un(satiable), beside, but,   continual, except, from, lest, neither, no more, none, not, nothing, save, that no, without.

h1116.definition: from an unused root (meaning to be high); an elevation; height, high place, wave.

h1117.definition: the same as {{h1116}}; Bamah, a place in Palestine; Bamah. See also {{h1120}}.

h1118.definition: probably from {{h4107}} with prepositional prefix; with pruning; Bimhal, an Israelite; Bimhal.

h1119.definition: prolongation for prepositional prefix; in, with, by, etc.; for, in into, through.

h1120.definition: plural of {{h1116}}; heights; or (fully) בָּמוֹת בַּעַל; from the same and {{h1168}}; heights of Baal; Bamoth or Bamoth-Baal, a place East of the Jordan; Bamoth, Bamoth-baal.

h1121.definition: from {{h1129}}; a son (as a builder of the family name), in the widest sense (of literal and figurative relationship, including grandson, subject, nation, quality or condition, etc., (like father or brother), etc.); afflicted, age, (Ahoh-) (Ammon-) (Hachmon-) (Lev-) ite, (anoint-) ed one, appointed to, ( ) arrow, (Assyr-) (Babylon-) (Egypt-) (Grec-) ian, one born, bough, branch, breed,   (young) bullock,   (young) calf, × came up in, child, colt, × common, × corn, daughter, × of first,   firstborn, foal,   very fruitful,   postage, × in,   kid,   lamb, ( ) man, meet,   mighty,   nephew, old, ( ) people,   rebel,   robber, × servant born, × soldier, son,   spark,   steward,   stranger, × surely, them of,   tumultuous one,   valiant(-est), whelp, worthy, young (one), youth.

h1122.definition: the same as {{h1121}}; Ben, an Israelite; Ben.

h1124.definition: (Aramaic) or בְּנָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h1129}}; to build; build, make.

h1125.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h40}}; (the) son of Abinadab; Ben-Abinadab, an Israelite; the son of Abinadab.

h1126.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h205}}; son of my sorrow; Ben-Oni, the original name of Benjamin; Ben-oni.

h1127.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h1397}}; son of (the) hero; Ben-Geber, an Israelite; the son of Geber.

h1128.definition: from {{h1121}} and a derivative of {{h1856}}; son of piercing (or of a lance); Ben-Deker, an Israelite; the son of Dekar.

h1129.definition: a primitive root; to build (literally and figuratively); (begin to) build(-er), obtain children, make, repair, set (up), × surely.

h1130.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h1908}}; son of Hadad; Ben-Hadad, the name of several Syrian kings; Benhadad.

h1131.definition: from {{h1129}}; built up; Binnui, an Israelite; Binnui.

h1132.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h2105}}; son of Zocheth; Ben-Zocheth, an Israelite; Ben-zoketh.

h1133.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h2354}}; son of Chur; Ben-Chur, an Israelite; the son of Hur.

h1134.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h2428}}; son of might; Ben-Chail, an Israelite; Ben-hail.

h1135.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h2605}}; son of Chanan; Ben-Chanan, an Israelite; Ben-hanan.

h1136.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h2617}}; son of kindness; Ben-Chesed, an Israelite; the son of Hesed.

h1137.definition: from {{h1129}}; built; Bani, the name of five Israelites; Bani.

h1138.definition: or (fuller) בּוּנִי; from {{h1129}}; built; Bunni or Buni, an Israelite; Bunni.

h1139.definition: from the plural construction of {{h1121}} and {{h1300}}; sons of lightning, Bene-berak, a place in Palestine; Bene-barak.

h1141.definition: or בּנָיָהוּ; (prolonged) from {{h1129}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has built; Benajah, the name of twelve Israelites; Benaiah.

h1142.definition: from the plural of {{h1121}} and {{h3292}}; sons of Yaakan; Bene-Jaakan, a place in the Desert; Bene-jaakan.

h1143.definition: dual of {{h996}}; a double interval, i.e. the space between two armies; + champion.

h1144.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h3225}}; son of (the) right hand; Binjamin, youngest son of Jacob; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory; Benjamin.

h1145.definition: sometimes (with the article inserted) בֵּן־הַיּמִינִי; with {{h376}} inserted (1 Samuel 9:1) בֶּן־אִישׁ ימִינִי; son of a man of Jemini; or shortened אִישׁ יְמִינִי; (1 Samuel 9:4; Esther 2:5) a man of Jemini, or (1 Samuel 20:1) simply יְמִינִיxlit Yᵉmînîy corrected to Yᵉmîynîy; a Jeminite; (plural) בְּנֵי יְמִינִיxlit Bᵉnîy corrected to Bᵉnêy; patron from {{h1144}}; a Benjaminite, or descendent of Benjamin; Benjamite, of Benjamin.

h1148.definition: probably from {{h1121}} with pron. suff.; our son; Beninu, an Israelite; Beninu.

h1149.definition: (Aramaic) of uncertain affinity; to be enraged; be angry.

h1150.definition: or בִּנְעָה; of uncertain derivation; Bina or Binah, an Israelite; Binea, Bineah.

h1151.definition: from {{h1121}} and {{h5971}} with pronomial suffix; son of my people; Ben-Ammi, a son of Lot; Ben-ammi.

h1152.definition: from {{h5475}} and {{h3050}} with prepositional prefix; in (the) counsel of Jehovah; Besodejah, an Israelite; Besodeiah.

h1153.definition: from {{h947}}; domineering; Besai, one of the Nethinim; Besai.

h1154.definition: from an unused root meaning to be sour; an immature grape; unripe grape.

h1155.definition: from the same as {{h1154}}; sour grape.

h1156.definition: (Aramaic) or בְּעָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h1158}}; to seek or ask; ask, desire, make (petition), pray, request, seek.

h1157.definition: from {{h5704}} with prepositional prefix; in up to or over against; generally at, beside, among, behind, for, etc.; about, at by (means of), for, over, through, up (-on), within.

h1158.definition: a primitive root; to gush over, i.e. to swell; (figuratively) to desire earnestly; by implication to ask; cause, inquire, seek up, swell out.

h1160.definition: from {{h1197}} (in the sense of burning); a lamp; Beor, the name of the father of an Edomitish king; also of that of Balaam; Beor.

h1162.definition: from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Boaz, the ancestor of David; also the name of a pillar in front of the temple; Boaz.

h1163.definition: a primitive root; to trample down, i.e. (figuratively) despise; kick.

h1165.definition: from {{h1197}} (in the sense of eating); cattle; beast, cattle.

h1166.definition: a primitive root; also as denominative from {{h1167}}; to be master; hence, to marry; have dominion (over), be husband, marry(-ried, × wife).

h1167.definition: from {{h1166}}; a master; hence, a husband, or (figuratively) owner (often used with another noun in modifications of this latter sense); archer,   babbler,   bird, captain, chief man,   confederate,   have to do,   dreamer, those to whom it is due,   furious, those that are given to it, great,   hairy, he that hath it, have,   horseman, husband, lord, man,   married, master, person,   sworn, they of.

h1168.definition: the same as {{h1167}}; Baal, a Phoenician deity; Baal, (plural) Baalim.

h1170.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h1285}}; Baal of (the) covenant; Baal-Berith, a special deity of the Shechemites; Baal-berith.

h1171.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h1409}}; Baal of Fortune; Baal-Gad, a place in Syria; Baal-gad.

h1172.definition: feminine of {{h1167}}; a mistress; that hath, mistress.

h1173.definition: the same as {{h1172}}; Baalah, the name of three places in Palestine; Baalah.

h1174.definition: from {{h1167}} and {{h1995}}; possessor of a multitude; Baal-Hamon, a place in Palestine; Baal-hamon.

h1175.definition: plural of {{h1172}}; mistresses; Bealoth, a place in Palestine; Bealoth, in Aloth (by mistake for a plural from {{h5927}} with prepositional prefix).

h1176.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h2070}}; Baal of (the) Fly; Baal-Zebub, a special deity of the Ekronites; Baal-zebub.

h1177.definition: from {{h1167}} and {{h2603}}; possessor of grace; Baal-Chanan, the name of an Edomite, also of an Israelite; Baal-hanan.

h1178.definition: from {{h1167}} and a modification of {{h2691}}; possessor of a village; Baal-Chatsor, a place in Palestine; Baal-hazor.

h1179.definition: from {{h1167}} and {{h2768}}; possessor of Hermon; Baal-Chermon, a place in Palestine; Baal-hermon.

h1180.definition: from {{h1167}} with pron. suff.; my master; Baali, a symbolical name for Jehovah; Baali.

h1181.definition: from the plural of {{h1168}} and the plural of {{h1116}}; Baals of (the) heights; Baale-Bamoth, a place East of the Jordan; lords of the high places.

h1182.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h3045}}; Baal has known; Beeljada, an Israelite; Beeliada.

h1183.definition: from {{h1167}} and {{h3050}}; Jah (is) master; Bealjah, an Israelite; Bealiah.

h1184.definition: from the plural of {{h1167}} and {{h3063}}; masters of Judah; Baale-Jehudah, a place in Palestine; Baale of Judah.

h1185.definition: probably from a derivative of {{h5965}} with prepositional prefix; in exultation; Baalis, an Ammonitish king; Baalis.

h1186.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h4583}}; Baal of (the) habitation (of) (compare {{h1010}}); Baal-Meon, a place East of the Jordan; Baal-meon.

h1187.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h6465}}; Baal of Peor; Baal-Peor, a Moabitish deity; Baal-peor.

h1188.definition: from {{h1167}} and the plural of {{h6556}}; possessor of breaches; Baal-Peratsim, a place in Palestine; Baal-perazim.

h1189.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h6828}} (in the sense of cold) (according to others an Egyptian form of Typhon, the destroyer); Baal of winter; Baal-Tsephon, a place in Eqypt; Baal-zephon.

h1190.definition: from {{h1168}} and {{h8031}}; Baal of Shalishah, Baal-Shalishah, a place in Palestine; Baal-shalisha.

h1191.definition: a modification of {{h1172}}; mistressship; Baalath, a place in Palestine; Baalath.

h1192.definition: from {{h1172}} and {{h875}}; mistress of a well; Baalath-Beer, a place in Palestine; Baalath-beer.

h1193.definition: from {{h1167}} and {{h8558}}; possessor of (the) palm-tree; Baal-Tamar, a place in Palestine; Baal-tamar.

h1194.definition: probably a contraction of {{h1010}}; Beön, a place East of the Jordan; Beon.

h1195.definition: the same as {{h1196}}; Baana, the name of four Israelite; Baana, Baanah.

h1196.definition: from a derivative of {{h6031}} with prepositional prefix; in affliction; Baanah, the name of four Israelites; Baanah.

h1197.definition: a primitive root; also as denominative from {{h1198}}; to kindle, i.e. consume (by fire or by eating); to be (-come) brutish; be brutish, bring (put, take) away, burn, (cause to) eat (up), feed, heat, kindle, set (on fire), waste.

h1198.definition: from {{h1197}}; properly, foot (as consumed); i.e. (by exten.) of cattle brutishness; (concretely) stupid; brutish (person), foolish.

h1199.definition: from {{h1198}}; brutish; Baara, an Israelitish woman; Baara.
